audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\codex-coherence-run.log:3305:audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\CRITIQUE_v2_SUMMARY.md:20:| `e4-v4-symmetric-frontier.mjs` | The lead table is still `D/C`; it contains central-win cells and later prints `0.95x`, `1.54x`, etc. (`audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design/v2-reproduction-e4-v4-symmetric-frontier.txt:1-17,47-57`). | Regression evidence for the old harm-weight model. It confirms a live multiplier-shaped reporting path, not v2 compliance. |
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\codex-coherence-run.log:3306:audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\CRITIQUE_v2_SUMMARY.md:58:The old `beta=1-eta` law equates two differential harm weights (`research/e4-analytical-backbone.md:41-60`). The new `a+bS+wZ` signal has no harm-weight parameter and does not nest that model. Under equal costs, a fixed funded share, and elliptical signals, a valid benchmark exists: parity is equality of `Cov(S,X_k)/sd(X_k)` across arms; with project-varying `Z`, this gives an implicit closed-form surface. Eligibility, heterogeneous costs, greedy residual-budget fill, MNAR Bernoulli reports, z-scoring, and credit make the full boundary a numerical expectation over discontinuous selection regions (`critique-v2-parity-boundary-analytic.md:11-170,172-202`).
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\codex-coherence-run.log:3307:audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\CRITIQUE_v2_SUMMARY.md:70:The written embargo applies `x` specifically to `Delta_O` while retaining `R=D/C`, leaving a formally compliant route to multiplier-first figures. The reproduced legacy engine exercises exactly that route (`v2-reproduction-e4-v4-symmetric-frontier.txt:1-17,47-57`).
