audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\codex-paper-integration-run.log:2784:+- **Faithfulness: VERIFIED.** The integrated subsections report the central's declared full-favourable endpoint as a central win at approximately 98% versus 68%, the probable reference as approximately 91% versus 45% for distributed and central, and the distributed-favourable case as positive distributed delivery against negative central value (`drafts/paper.md:631-637`; `drafts/paper.es.md:691-697`). `npm run e4:scenarios` reproduced the underlying 97.6%/68.1%, 91.2%/44.6%, and -104.0%/95.8% values. The prose also preserves the path-dependent sequential attribution: harm-myopia alone accounts for about 40% of the move, with the further competent no-myopia bundle accounting for the remaining approximately 60% (`drafts/paper.md:637-640`; `drafts/paper.es.md:697-701`). It places parity partway along the declared probable-to-central-favourable segment and labels the magnitudes as source-motivated declared reference and stress points, not calibrated bands (`drafts/paper.md:645-653`; `drafts/paper.es.md:705-714`).
audits/2026-07-11-v1.14-design\codex-paper-integration-run.log:2788:+- **No overclaim, dishonest label, or multiplier notation: VERIFIED.** The additions use the declared scenario labels, expose harm-myopia as the load-bearing and least empirically pinned assumption, and exclude administrative-cost and leakage channels. They introduce no multiplier-form `x`, `×`, or `D/C` notation and make no claim about a “best plausible” case, “where reality sits,” or calibrated impact.
