 568: regimes—not a point multiplier or calibrated impact.
 569: 
 570: **The symmetric credit-versus-coverage gate (methods and result).** Because this
 571: is the paper's one confirmatory computation, its design is stated in full here
 572: rather than only by reference. Each world holds K = 500 candidate projects; for
 573: each, N = 5000 potential participants are considered, each interested with a
 574: project-specific probability, so the interested reach is at most N and endogenous.
 575: Both arms then see the
 576: same candidate pool, the same exact costs, the same truth net[j] = S[j] − h·cost[j],
 577: delivery held at **parity**, and the same report noise report = v + Normal(0, τ);
 578: each funds a **greedy** set under a budget of one-third of total project cost, is
 579: eligible to fund a project only where *its own* noisy estimate of net is positive
 580: (no oracle gate), and its delivered value is scored on the projects' *true* net.
 581: The arms are symmetric except for the coverage mechanism and its matched
 582: counterparts. *Distributed (endogenous coverage):* each interested citizen reports
 583: independently with probability p if her value v ≥ 0 and p·(1 − β) if v < 0 (adverse
 584: voice bias), giving ĥS_D = Σreports / p, ranked by estimated net per cost.
 585: *Central (competent value-reader):* an appraisal budget matched to the distributed
 586: arm's *expected* total reports in that world, spread **evenly** across projects as a
 587: rounded fixed per-project bandwidth m_C = round(expected reports / K) (so the two
 588: arms' appraisal totals are equal in expectation up to that rounding); per project it
 589: samples m_C interested citizens, observes v + Normal(0, τ), and forms its own noisy
 590: ĥNet_C = reach·mean(observed) − h·cost. It ranks by score = (1 − λ)·z(ĥNet_C/cost) + λ·z(P/cost) — its **own noisy
 591: estimate**, never the true net — where P is claimable political credit (the
 592: electoral credit-claiming and traceability logic by which visible, attributable
 593: benefits are favoured over diffuse ones; Mayhew 1974; Arnold 1990) and λ is bounded
 594: credit pressure (a *posited* pressure whose real-world magnitude must be measured,
 595: not assumed). Credit moves *ranking*, never eligibility (no knowingly
 596: value-destroying planner). The legitimate asymmetries are therefore only these:
 597: distributed reports self-route to projects citizens care about while negative
 598: stakeholders participate less, and central appraisal is spread evenly while its
 599: ranking carries credit pressure — everything else is shared. The estimand is
 600: **Δ = (D − C)/O** per world, where D, C, O are delivered true net for the
 601: distributed, central, and full-information greedy arms and O is a reference level,
 602: not an optimum. The frozen grid sweeps λ ∈ {0, 0.1, 0.2, 0.3} (λ = 0 a negative
 603: control), a latent-correlation setting ρ ∈ {0, 0.5, 1} (realized corr(S, P) ≈ 0.00,
 604: 0.30, 0.82), and h ∈ {1.5, 2.5, 4} over 100 seeded worlds, in a baseline
 605: observation regime (p = .35, β = .30, τ = .5) and a matched-budget low-information
 606: stress regime (p = .15, β = .60, τ = 1.0). The **pre-registered decision rule** —
 607: frozen before running and designed by the independent auditor to be adversarial —
 608: required, for a GO on rebuilding the quantitative engine, at least 15 of the 18
 609: primary cells with mean Δ > 0, a pooled **median Δ ≥ 0.05**, a bootstrap lower
 610: bound > 0, and median Δ ≥ 0 under the stress regime, plus a guard to pause if the
 611: λ = 0 control itself exceeded 0.05. The result was **NO-GO**: the advantage was
 612: positive in all 18 primary cells, but the pre-registered pooled **median Δ = 0.025**,
 613: below the 0.05 rebuild gate; the λ = 0 negative control sat at ≈ 0.016, within the
 614: pause guard (no hidden asymmetry flagged). A **post-hoc** world-cluster
 615: ratio-of-sums estimate was Δ = 0.026 [0.023, 0.029] (Monte-Carlo uncertainty on the
 616: simulated data-generating process, reported separately from the median). The
 617: advantage rises with credit pressure λ and falls as credit aligns with value — the
 618: credit-versus-coverage mechanism — but it is small, which is why the calibrated
 619: multiplier is retired and the paper rests on the architecture and the mechanism
